e creation of visual media, such as animation or webpages. Continue reading to learn more about an education and career opportunities in visual communication design. Inside Visual Communication Design Visual communication design is a key component of multimedia development, including digital publishing and video games. Visual communication design professionals create images with the objective of conveying a message through the shapes, colors, text, organization and other elements in the image. They often plan, analyze and create visual solutions to communications problems. Some use computer software to develop the overall layout and production design of newspapers and magazines. Others produce promotional displays and marketing brochures for advertising campaigns or design distinctive logos for products and services. Education Information Studies of visual communication design can be found at the certificate and associate's, bachelor's and graduate degree levels. These programs train students in the use of specialized software and tools related to visual communications, as well as providing them with the theory necessary to convey messages effectively. Course topics include graphic design principles, photography, communication fundamentals and typography. These Study.com articles explore some of the degree opportunities available in visual communication design. Visual Communication Certificate Visual Communication Associate's Degree Program Visual Communication Bachelor's Degree Program Master's Degree in Visual Communication Distance Learning Options Half-online, half-in-class programs (hybrid programs) focusing on visual communication design are available, along with some entirely online options. There are also free courses that can expand a student's understanding of communication theory. These articles deal with some of these options regarding visual communication theory. Online BFA in Visual Communication Free Online Communications Classes Online Visual Communication Undergraduate Program Online Visual Communication Degree Career Options Visual communication students may join the ranks of traditional media, such as publishing, or become a part of the digital revolution for media and advertising. The following links detail a few possible career paths for visual communication students. Visual Communications Designer Visual Communication Design Technician Careers in Visual Communication Design Employment Outlook and Salary Information According to the U.S. Bureau of Labor Statistics (BLS), the number of jobs in the field of visual communications (which includes graphic designers, animators and art directors, among others) was expected to increase at a slower-than-average pace compared with the average of other career fields (www.bls.gov). The BLS reported that in May 2013, the middle half of graphic designers had annual salaries between $34,040 and $60,510. The middle half of multimedia artists earned between $46,590 and $88,750. Read more General Visual Communications Design Related Articles RelatedRelated Articles Recently UpdatedRecent Articles PopularPopular Articles Top School in San Diego for Graphic Design & Visual Communications Seven schools in the San Diego, CA, area have top ranking graphic design and visual communications programs. Read on to find out what one... Top Graphic Design and Visual Communications Degree - Chicago, IL Students interested in studying graphic design and visual communications in Chicago, IL, have many schools to choose from. Read about the... Career Information for a Degree in Visual Communications Design Visual communications design degree programs generally cover illustration, graphic design, art direction and animation. Continue reading... Visual Communications Major Visual Communications Courses in Grand Rapids, MI Visual Communications Degree in Connecticut Distance Learning Visual Communications Undergraduate Degree Visual Communication Design Masters Visual Communications Certificat